    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "# Set seed for reproducibility\n",
    "np.random.seed(42)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Generate synthetic data\n",
    "num_students = 100\n",
    "lectures_attended = np.random.randint(0, 31, size=num_students)  # out of 30 lectures\n",
    "# Simulate marks out of 20, with positive correlation to lectures attended + some noise\n",
    "marks_obtained = np.clip((lectures_attended * 0.6 + np.random.normal(0, 2, size=num_students)), 0, 20)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Create dataframe\n",
    "df = pd.DataFrame({\n",
    "\n",
    "    'Lectures_Attended': lectures_attended,\n",
    "    'Marks_Obtained': marks_obtained.round(2)\n",
    "})\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Save to CSV\n",
    "df.to_csv('lecture_marks_dataset.csv', index=False)\n",
    "print(\"Dataset saved as 'lecture_marks_dataset.csv'\")"
   ]
  },

    "def categorize(marks):\n",
    "    if marks >= 17:\n",
    "        return 'Excellent'\n",
    "    elif marks >= 13:\n",
    "        return 'Good'\n",
    "    elif marks >= 9:\n",
    "        return 'Average'\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        return 'Poor'\n",
    "\n",
    "df['Category'] = df['Marks_Obtained'].apply(categorize)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Count the number of students in each category\n",
    "category_counts = df['Category'].value_counts()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot pie chart\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(7, 7))\n",
    "plt.pie(category_counts, labels=category_counts.index, autopct='%1.1f%%', startangle=90,\n",
    "        colors=['#4CAF50', '#2196F3', '#FFC107', '#F44336'])\n",
    "plt.title('Student Performance Categories (Marks Out of 20)')\n",
    "plt.axis('equal')  # Circle\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
